C Language Fundamentals (3 Questions)
Write a C program that takes principal amount, rate of interest, and time in years as input and calculates the simple interest. Use appropriate data types for all variables.
Write a program that converts a temperature from Celsius to Fahrenheit. The formula is F = (C * 9/5) + 32.
Write a program to take a decimal number as input and convert it into its binary representation.
Control Structures (3 Questions)
Write a program to check if a given year is a leap year or not. A year is a leap year if it is divisible by 4, except for end-of-century years, which must be divisible by 400.
Write a program to create a simple calculator that performs addition, subtraction, multiplication, or division based on user input. The user should enter two numbers and an operator (+, -, *, /). Use a switch statement to handle the operations.
