text

*
**
***
****
*****
Functions (3 Questions)
Write a function int isPrime(int n) that takes an integer n as input and returns 1 if the number is prime and 0 otherwise. Use this function in your main() to check a number entered by the user.
Write a function void findMinMax(int arr[], int size, int* min, int* max) that finds the minimum and maximum elements in an array. The results should be stored in the variables pointed to by min and max.
Write a function to calculate the power of a number (a^b) without using the pow() library function. The function should take the base and exponent as arguments.
Arrays (3 Questions)
Write a program to read N integers into a one-dimensional array and then reverse the array in-place (i.e., without using a second array).
Write a program to add two 3x3 matrices. You will need to declare three 2D arrays: two for the input matrices and one for the result.
Write a program to find the second largest element in a one-dimensional integer array.
Pointers (3 Questions)
Write a function void swap(int *a, int *b) that swaps the values of two integer variables using pointers. Call this function from main() to demonstrate its usage.
Write a program to find the length of a string using a pointer. Do not use the strlen() library function.
Write a function that takes an integer array and its size as input and returns the sum of all its elements. Use pointer arithmetic to traverse the array instead of array indexing (arr[i]).
Structures and Unions (3 Questions)
Define a structure named Book with members title (char array), author (char array), and price (float). Write a program to read the details of 3 books and display the details of the book with the highest price.
Define a structure Student with members roll_no, name, and an array of 5 integers for marks in 5 subjects. Write a program to read the data for one student and calculate their total marks and percentage.
Define a union named DataType that can hold an int, a float, and a char. Write a program to demonstrate that only one member of the union can be used at a time by assigning a value to the integer member, printing it, then assigning a value to the float member, and printing all members again to observe the corrupted data.
File Handling (3 Questions)
Write a program that asks the user to enter a line of text and saves it to a file named log.txt. If the file already exists, the new text should be appended to the end of the file.
Write a program that reads a text file named source.txt and counts the total number of characters, spaces, and lines in it.
Write a program to copy the contents of one file (source.txt) to another file (destination.txt). The program should handle cases where the source file does not exist.
String Handling (3 Questions)
Write a program to concatenate two strings into a third string without using the strcat() library function.
Write a program to check if a given string is a palindrome (reads the same forwards and backward), ignoring case. For example, "Madam" should be considered a palindrome.
Write a program that takes a string as input and counts the frequency of each character in it.
Recursion (3 Questions)
Write a recursive function to calculate the factorial of a non-negative integer.
Write a recursive function to generate the Nth term in the Fibonacci sequence (0, 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, ...).
Write a recursive function int multiply(int a, int b) that calculates the product of two integers without using the * operator. You can use addition and subtraction. (Hint: a * b is a added to itself b times).




